♪ Oh, Susanna,
Oh, don't you cry for me ♪

769
01:04:00,552 --> 01:04:03,538
♪ I come from Alabama
with a banjo on my knee ♪

770
01:04:06,108 --> 01:04:09,929
♪ Oh, Susanna,
Oh, don't you cry for me ♪

771
01:04:10,028 --> 01:04:13,099
♪ I come from Alabama
with a banjo on my knee ♪

772
01:04:13,199 --> 01:04:17,503
♪ I drove across a telegraph
and traveled down the river ♪

773
01:04:17,603 --> 01:04:19,438
♪ Electric fluid magnified ♪

774
01:04:19,538 --> 01:04:21,206
♪ And killed
five hundred chigger ♪

775
01:04:21,306 --> 01:04:25,110
♪ Oh, Susanna,
oh, don't you cry for me ♪

776
01:04:25,210 --> 01:04:27,313
♪ I come from Alabama
with a banjo on my knee... ♪

777
01:04:27,413 --> 01:04:28,413
Bass.

778
01:04:29,347 --> 01:04:32,117
You hear a single word of this?

779
01:04:32,217 --> 01:04:34,420
I apologize, man.

780
01:04:34,519 --> 01:04:38,190
Thought I was gonna have to have
a word with Charlie over there.

781
01:04:38,291 --> 01:04:41,960
He's quite a character,
isn't he?

782
01:04:42,061 --> 01:04:46,498
You know that man you seek?
He's as bad as they come.

783
01:04:46,599 --> 01:04:49,467
We come from the same place,

784
01:04:49,568 --> 01:04:52,038
breathe the same air.

785
01:04:52,137 --> 01:04:55,007
If he's as bad
as you say he is,

786
01:04:55,106 --> 01:04:57,425
what that make me?

787
01:04:59,563 --> 01:05:00,563
Huh?!

788
01:05:03,199 --> 01:05:07,085
Dick Lassen is as mean as
that man's pinkie toe.

789
01:05:07,186 --> 01:05:09,288
Now, I don't run from
a fight, you know that.

790
01:05:09,387 --> 01:05:11,224
But I would not pursue him.

791
01:05:11,324 --> 01:05:13,425
I ain't ever met
a man that mean.

792
01:05:13,525 --> 01:05:15,260
Or that fast.

793
01:05:15,360 --> 01:05:17,096
Not even you, Bass.

794
01:05:17,195 --> 01:05:18,755
Well, you haven't
seen me for a while.

795
01:05:18,530 --> 01:05:20,481
No. No, I haven't.

796
01:05:22,219 --> 01:05:25,905
Look, he sent a man's head

797
01:05:26,005 --> 01:05:30,041
with a badge attached
to his eye to a judge.

798
01:05:30,141 --> 01:05:33,612
Don't you never mind,
'cause I don't know where he is.

799
01:05:33,713 --> 01:05:36,030
Not many do.

800
01:05:45,574 --> 01:05:46,574
Whoa.

801
01:05:49,045 --> 01:05:51,664
Whoa, easy guys.

802
01:05:51,764 --> 01:05:52,764
Easy.

803
01:05:56,954 --> 01:05:58,552
It's just me.

804
01:06:01,958 --> 01:06:04,224
I have a message for Dozier.

805
01:06:10,599 --> 01:06:16,021
Any creature
that would leave to die, the delegate,

806
01:06:16,121 --> 01:06:19,541
they warrant any punishment
that befalls them.

807
01:06:41,731 --> 01:06:45,199
Negro, speaks Creek...

808
01:06:49,039 --> 01:06:51,206
shot five men before
they could draw.

809
01:06:53,309 --> 01:06:55,076
Right,
and he's looking for me.

810
01:06:57,313 --> 01:07:00,414
Well, I guess my last message
wasn't loud enough.

811
01:07:02,052 --> 01:07:04,719
Government man wants
to find me, Negro or not...

812
01:07:06,655 --> 01:07:09,608
well, I'll make it easy for 'em.

813
01:07:09,708 --> 01:07:13,108
♪ Oh... Susanna ♪

814
01:07:13,545 --> 01:07:16,297
♪ Oh, don't you cry for me ♪

815
01:07:18,568 --> 01:07:23,356
♪ I come from Alabama
with a banjo on my knee ♪

816
01:07:23,456 --> 01:07:26,291
How come you ain't
singing, Bass?

817
01:07:26,391 --> 01:07:28,760
Why aren't you having any fun?

818
01:07:28,860 --> 01:07:31,163
How come you never
have any fun, Bass?

819
01:07:31,262 --> 01:07:34,262
♪ Oh, Susanna ♪

820
01:07:35,166 --> 01:07:37,585
♪ Oh, don't you cry for me ♪

821
01:07:41,557 --> 01:07:45,378
♪ Oh, I jumped aboard a telegraph ♪

822
01:07:45,478 --> 01:07:48,563
♪ And traveled down the river ♪

823
01:07:50,400 --> 01:07:55,570
♪ Electric fluid magnified
and killed 500 chigger ♪

824
01:07:57,373 --> 01:08:00,159
Hey, Bass, did you hear me?

825
01:08:00,259 --> 01:08:03,177
No "nigger," "chigger."

826
01:08:05,382 --> 01:08:08,782
♪ Kill 500 chigger ♪

827
01:08:11,253 --> 01:08:13,239
Hey, Bass, the horses.

828
01:08:13,338 --> 01:08:14,639
We left the horses back there--

829
01:08:14,739 --> 01:08:16,442
They're gonna be just fine.

830
01:08:16,542 --> 01:08:18,181
- Okay.
- We'll get them in the morning.

831
01:08:17,842 --> 01:08:20,042
Okay. Okay.

832
01:08:20,179 --> 01:08:21,179
Okay.

833
01:08:24,201 --> 01:08:25,400
Hey...

834
01:08:28,404 --> 01:08:29,804
You're all right.

835
01:08:32,109 --> 01:08:34,208
You're all right, Bass.

836
01:08:36,512 --> 01:08:37,512
Bass.

837
01:08:41,585 --> 01:08:42,585
Yeah.

838
01:08:45,822 --> 01:08:48,555
What is it, Sam?

839
01:08:52,662 --> 01:08:55,747
I just never thought of you
as a law man.

840
01:08:55,847 --> 01:08:58,332
Not after what the law
did to you.

841
01:08:59,703 --> 01:09:02,136
The law put me in chains.

842
01:09:03,840 --> 01:09:07,126
But the law also set me free.

843
01:09:07,225 --> 01:09:10,162
Now, I got six little ones,
and I need to stay free.

844
01:09:10,261 --> 01:09:11,261
Six?

845
01:09:11,729 --> 01:09:14,166
Gracious, Bass,

846
01:09:14,265 --> 01:09:16,818
you wearing that poor woman
out, ain't you?

847
01:09:29,198 --> 01:09:31,783
I hear there's a black boy
seeking my whereabouts.

848
01:09:31,884 --> 01:09:33,684
It's him.

849
01:09:42,444 --> 01:09:44,329
It's Dozier!

850
01:09:44,430 --> 01:09:45,430
No.

851
01:09:47,184 --> 01:09:48,850
Seek no more, here I am.

852
01:10:04,701 --> 01:10:05,701
Bass?

853
01:10:07,737 --> 01:10:10,555
He rides into my town,
we'll take him together, Bass.

854
01:10:10,655 --> 01:10:14,560
No, he rides into your town
for me, it's me he gets.

855
01:10:14,659 --> 01:10:16,828
You can't face him alone.

856
01:10:16,929 --> 01:10:20,599
Even if I can't,
you with your one arm,

857
01:10:20,698 --> 01:10:22,701
it's not gonna be much help.

858
01:10:22,801 --> 01:10:24,720
I can shoot with one
better than most with two,

859
01:10:24,703 --> 01:10:26,438
you know that, Bass.

860
01:10:26,537 --> 01:10:28,537
Sixkiller,

861
01:10:29,341 --> 01:10:32,444
you saved a drowning boy once.

862
01:10:32,543 --> 01:10:34,561
Let that man repay you.

863
01:10:35,966 --> 01:10:37,550
You got two minutes.

864
01:10:37,649 --> 01:10:39,333
I won't need 'em.

865
01:10:54,251 --> 01:10:56,016
Don't tell me
you went coward on me.

866
01:11:14,871 --> 01:11:18,289
Well, I'll be damned.

867
01:11:18,390 --> 01:11:20,807
That young Indian was right.

868
01:11:23,445 --> 01:11:26,332
A Negro on a quest for me.

869
01:11:26,431 --> 01:11:28,048
Bob Dozier...

870
01:11:30,287 --> 01:11:33,954
I have a warrant for your arrest.

871
01:11:36,960 --> 01:11:39,511
A Negro with that warrant
has no authority here.

872
01:11:39,610 --> 01:11:40,761
Oh, but he does.

873
01:11:42,631 --> 01:11:44,798
And so do I.

874
01:11:50,873 --> 01:11:53,891
I'm gonna
excuse your ignorance,

875
01:11:53,992 --> 01:11:55,909
give you a chance
to claim your life.

876
01:11:58,014 --> 01:12:00,966
Thank you, Mr. Dozier.

877
01:12:01,065 --> 01:12:02,949
I will return.

878
01:12:07,524 --> 01:12:10,809
But not without executing
this warrant.

879
01:12:10,908 --> 01:12:14,309
Dead... or alive.

880
01:12:20,470 --> 01:12:22,320
Is that the way
you want it to be?

881
01:12:22,421 --> 01:12:24,439
That's the way it is.

882
01:12:42,658 --> 01:12:44,826
Your move, boy.

883
01:13:37,514 --> 01:13:39,046
Dead or alive.

884
01:13:40,082 --> 01:13:42,582
Got one, boy!

885
01:15:29,692 --> 01:15:32,511
Bass hasn't
been seen in a week,

886
01:15:32,610 --> 01:15:34,512
and he's feared dead.

887
01:15:34,613 --> 01:15:37,731
President Grant will be here
in two days.

888
01:16:22,878 --> 01:16:24,845
Let's take him together, Bass.

889
01:16:26,716 --> 01:16:30,184
Sixkiller, you saved
a drowning boy once.

890
01:16:51,039 --> 01:16:55,193
♪ Will be all right ♪

891
01:16:55,292 --> 01:16:57,493
♪ Pray on ♪

892
01:16:59,831 --> 01:17:01,381
Where are you off to?

893
01:17:07,023 --> 01:17:09,942
Thought you were still asleep.

894
01:17:10,042 --> 01:17:12,059
Well, I'm up now.

895
01:17:14,730 --> 01:17:18,198
Spanish Fort,
about a half a day's ride.

896
01:17:22,671 --> 01:17:24,971
You thinking about going alone?

897
01:17:27,310 --> 01:17:29,293
Well, you got one arm,

898
01:17:29,394 --> 01:17:30,962
you liquored,

899
01:17:31,063 --> 01:17:33,247
you'll slow me down.

900
01:17:35,952 --> 01:17:37,885
All right.

901
01:17:39,421 --> 01:17:41,322
Go on, then...

902
01:17:44,027 --> 01:17:47,028
make a widow of your wife,
orphan of them kids.

903
01:17:50,332 --> 01:17:51,533
Go on!

904
01:17:52,216 --> 01:17:54,752
Bad-ass Bass Reeves.

905
01:17:54,853 --> 01:17:57,671
The man who rides
with nobody by his side.

906
01:17:59,207 --> 01:18:02,342
Shit. Well, go on.

907
01:18:04,346 --> 01:18:08,948
He may be slow of tongue,
but his words are sharp.

908
01:18:11,453 --> 01:18:14,405
Now, Dozier
may have some men,

909
01:18:14,506 --> 01:18:15,974
but he don't need
them anymore--

910
01:18:16,073 --> 01:18:17,992
Well, what good are you?!

911
01:18:19,362 --> 01:18:21,979
You got one arm.

912
01:18:22,079 --> 01:18:24,364
You can't even go a day
without drinking.

913
01:18:26,469 --> 01:18:28,819
The border's right there.

914
01:18:28,920 --> 01:18:30,822
Why don't you run?

915
01:18:30,921 --> 01:18:33,340
You don't have to finish.

916
01:18:40,115 --> 01:18:44,970
Buddy, I seen what you did
to Dozier's men.

917
01:18:45,069 --> 01:18:48,172
If you only had some help.

918
01:18:48,273 --> 01:18:51,710
I mean, what I'm trying
to say is,

919
01:18:51,810 --> 01:18:53,278
if you insist on going

920
01:18:53,377 --> 01:18:55,762
after what you now know...

921
01:18:57,500 --> 01:18:59,451
then fuck it!

922
01:18:59,551 --> 01:19:01,420
I'll go too.

923
01:19:01,520 --> 01:19:04,722
But we better pray
my boots become unstuck.

924
01:19:04,823 --> 01:19:08,025
Yeah, I could run.
I could be headed for the border.

925
01:19:08,126 --> 01:19:10,261
Keep taking what I want,

926
01:19:10,362 --> 01:19:13,899
shoot anybody who doesn't
want to give it to me.

927
01:19:13,998 --> 01:19:17,034
Or maybe
I could do something.

928
01:19:17,135 --> 01:19:19,871
You know, something...

929
01:19:19,970 --> 01:19:23,041
Worthy...
of a proper obit.

930
01:19:23,140 --> 01:19:24,140
Huh?

931
01:19:26,194 --> 01:19:27,994
Something worth writing about.

932
01:19:32,435 --> 01:19:35,301
Why don't you go home?
You're the one with the family.

933
01:19:36,773 --> 01:19:39,990
Leave this fool's errand
to this coward here.

934
01:19:40,091 --> 01:19:43,210
And this old drunk outlaw.

935
01:19:51,887 --> 01:19:54,488
If I leave...

936
01:19:55,239 --> 01:19:58,091
Who's gonna save ya
from the fool's folly?

937
01:20:00,029 --> 01:20:01,828
Thatta boy!

938
01:20:05,100 --> 01:20:06,900
Thatta boy.

939
01:20:15,011 --> 01:20:16,011
Yow!

940
01:21:01,224 --> 01:21:03,341
"I'll annointest my hand with oil.

941
01:21:03,440 --> 01:21:06,011
My cup runneth over.

942
01:21:06,110 --> 01:21:08,814
Surely goodness and mercy
shall follow me

943
01:21:08,913 --> 01:21:11,198
all the days of my life."

944
01:21:59,215 --> 01:22:02,234
40 men on three.

945
01:22:02,333 --> 01:22:05,302
That's not odds I'd take
if I was a gambler.

946
01:22:05,403 --> 01:22:08,305
Yeah, you win at them odds,
you a legend.

947
01:22:08,405 --> 01:22:12,243
All right,
we wait till nightfall,

948
01:22:12,344 --> 01:22:14,578
circle the town,

949
01:22:14,679 --> 01:22:17,515
then we jump them
before daybreak.

950
01:22:17,614 --> 01:22:20,585
That's it?
That's what you want to do?

951
01:22:20,685 --> 01:22:22,970
That's why we came.

952
01:22:25,373 --> 01:22:27,626
We circled this before,
and there were six of us,

953
01:22:27,725 --> 01:22:29,261
or five.

954
01:22:29,360 --> 01:22:31,595
And he was alone.

955
01:22:31,695 --> 01:22:33,899
And he still lives.

956
01:22:33,998 --> 01:22:35,900
Did you go in by surprise?

957
01:22:36,001 --> 01:22:37,668
No, the stupid bastard
announced--

958
01:22:37,769 --> 01:22:40,905
Well, you don't knock
on the Devil's door and ask to come in.

959
01:22:41,006 --> 01:22:44,242
You wait till nightfall.

960
01:22:44,341 --> 01:22:47,444
You go in real quiet-like,
you take out every man that's posted.

961
01:22:47,545 --> 01:22:50,015
You make your way
through the house,

962
01:22:50,114 --> 01:22:53,284
you get to his bedroom,
you surround the motherfucker,

963
01:22:53,385 --> 01:22:56,020
he comes out with you.

964
01:22:56,121 --> 01:22:58,072
Dead or alive.

965
01:22:59,542 --> 01:23:02,309
Nightfall it is.

966
01:23:18,159 --> 01:23:22,159
♪ There was a time ♪

967
01:23:25,216 --> 01:23:30,216
♪ Everything so supreme ♪

968
01:23:33,123 --> 01:23:35,292
Man: And I threw that man
right through the window.

969
01:23:35,393 --> 01:23:38,128
Then the boss rides up,
lights some dynamite,

970
01:23:38,229 --> 01:23:40,030
tosses it in the house,

971
01:23:40,131 --> 01:23:42,067
we ride off, and then boom!

972
01:23:42,167 --> 01:23:44,168
Whole ground shook.

973
01:23:44,269 --> 01:23:46,119
Is that it?

974
01:24:18,487 --> 01:24:20,704
One for me, and one for--

975
01:24:20,805 --> 01:24:22,756
No, I'm good.

976
01:24:25,261 --> 01:24:28,479
I'm gonna go sleep off this fun.

977
01:24:28,579 --> 01:24:31,716
The stage comes through tomorrow.

978
01:24:31,815 --> 01:24:34,568
We pull this off my way,
this town eats for a year.

979
01:24:45,847 --> 01:24:49,400
♪ You may run for a long time ♪

980
01:24:49,501 --> 01:24:52,569
♪ Run on for a long time ♪

981
01:24:52,670 --> 01:24:56,207
♪ Run on for a long time ♪

982
01:24:56,306 --> 01:25:00,412
♪ Let me tell you that God's
gonna cut you down ♪

983
01:25:00,511 --> 01:25:05,682
♪ Let me tell you that God's
gonna cut you down ♪

984
01:25:05,783 --> 01:25:08,702
That's about gonnavdo it for me.

985
01:25:10,805 --> 01:25:14,324
♪ My God spoke and He
spoke so sweet ♪

986
01:25:14,425 --> 01:25:17,295
♪ I thought I heard the shuffle
of angels' feet ♪

987
01:25:17,395 --> 01:25:20,364
♪ And he put hand
upon my head ♪

988
01:25:20,465 --> 01:25:24,335
♪ Great God almighty,
I'll tell you what he said ♪

989
01:25:24,435 --> 01:25:26,237
It's time.

990
01:25:26,337 --> 01:25:29,573
♪ Go tell
her long tongue liar ♪

991
01:25:29,673 --> 01:25:32,342
♪ Tell that midnight rider ♪

992
01:25:32,443 --> 01:25:34,212
♪ Tell the gamblers, the ramblers ♪

993
01:25:34,311 --> 01:25:36,213
♪ The back biters ♪

994
01:25:36,314 --> 01:25:39,565
♪ Tell them that God's
gonna cut them down ♪

995
01:25:42,337 --> 01:25:44,756
Look a little lost there, fella.

996
01:25:44,855 --> 01:25:46,591
I'm just passing through.

997
01:25:46,690 --> 01:25:49,091
You the law?

998
01:25:49,293 --> 01:25:52,162
I don't know of any colored
lawmen around these parts.

999
01:25:52,262 --> 01:25:53,863
Come on.

1000
01:25:54,666 --> 01:25:56,865
Oh! Easy...

1001
01:25:57,702 --> 01:26:00,771
If you've come for Dozier,
we ain't got no quarrel.

1002
01:26:00,872 --> 01:26:03,541
I do what I do out here
just not to die.

1003
01:26:03,640 --> 01:26:05,510
Where does Dozier
keep his horse?

1004
01:26:05,609 --> 01:26:07,811
Outside his house.

1005
01:26:07,912 --> 01:26:09,713
Especially since that
marshal showed up,

1006
01:26:09,814 --> 01:26:11,532
woods are dangerous over there.

1007
01:26:19,408 --> 01:26:21,341
You're a lucky man.

1008
01:27:46,929 --> 01:27:49,429
Lord,
tell me if I should act now.

1009
01:27:56,738 --> 01:27:59,356
I'm sorry, Lord.

1010
01:27:59,457 --> 01:28:01,774
I was kind of hoping
you'd be louder.

1011
01:28:04,579 --> 01:28:07,046
But you didn't say no.

1012
01:28:48,524 --> 01:28:51,557
You killed a dear
friend of mine.

1013
01:28:53,028 --> 01:28:55,028
You tried to kill me too.

1014
01:28:56,765 --> 01:28:58,349
You didn't die.

1015
01:28:58,448 --> 01:29:01,019
Like I said before,

1016
01:29:01,118 --> 01:29:04,588
I'm here to return you to Fort Smith.

1017
01:29:04,689 --> 01:29:08,626
By the power given me
by the Federal Court.

1018
01:29:08,725 --> 01:29:10,877
You can cackle all you want.

1019
01:29:13,047 --> 01:29:15,832
You and no Federal Court
has any jurisdiction over me.

1020
01:29:15,932 --> 01:29:18,652
Then maybe I'll just
shoot you dead now.

1021
